column5: Does anyone have information on Longbow Lake. This is a lake just off the northeastern part of LOW. I also need to know if a 14ft boat would be too small for this lake.
Does anyone have information on Longbow Lake. This is a lake just off the northeastern part of LOW. I also need to know if a 14ft boat would be too small for this lake.

Tjsker, We are going to Longbow for the first time in June. Usually stay up the road about 20 miles but resort we go to is getting run down, time for a change. Got maps from area resort owners, lake looks easy to navigate and is fairly well protected. You do have accesss to LOW. I think you would be fine with the 14' as long as you didn't venture to far into LOW. Anybody out there that has any more info I would appreciate it too!
